1
00:00:00,458 --> 00:00:02,250
They brought us here
and I didn’t know the place

2
00:00:02,541 --> 00:00:05,958
They took me in through
here—there was a parking lot

3
00:00:06,875 --> 00:00:08,375
They had seized it

4
00:00:09,166 --> 00:00:11,125
We stood in the yard after they
unloaded us from the vehicle

5
00:00:11,708 --> 00:00:14,458
There were about seven to
eight of us when they brought us

6
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:16,000
They had brought
people from another hall

7
00:00:16,750 --> 00:00:20,458
They made us enter with our heads lowered,
our hands shackled, and our eyes blindfolded

8
00:00:20,500 --> 00:00:22,041
They brought us
in through this door

9
00:00:22,625 --> 00:00:26,166
They led us from here and took
us up the stairs to the hall above

10
00:00:27,541 --> 00:00:30,625
I served my sentence in the hall

11
00:00:42,333 --> 00:00:44,041
Interviewer: When you
entered this courtyard

12
00:00:45,166 --> 00:00:48,375
Did you enter the yard and corridor
while your eyes were blindfolded?

13
00:00:49,416 --> 00:00:51,000
And your hands were shackled?

14
00:00:51,041 --> 00:00:57,375
If your eyes were blindfolded, what
sounds could you hear around you?

15
00:00:58,666 --> 00:01:02,250
They brought me in with my eyes
blindfolded and my hands shackled

16
00:01:03,125 --> 00:01:08,333
They took us in through here and I could
hear the sounds of flogging and their chatter

17
00:01:09,166 --> 00:01:10,833
But I didn’t know what
they were talking about

18
00:01:11,500 --> 00:01:16,125
The sound of cleaning weapons
and the click of their walkie-talkies

19
00:01:16,166 --> 00:01:17,333
Which they used to call with

20
00:01:18,250 --> 00:01:21,333
They made us go up a bit here,
then continued with us to the hall

21
00:01:21,541 --> 00:01:22,416
Interviewer: Okay

22
00:01:24,708 --> 00:01:29,166
Do you remember the ISIS members
present, their names and nationalities?

23
00:01:31,791 --> 00:01:32,958
Their appearance?

24
00:01:33,250 --> 00:01:34,791
They were all masked

25
00:01:35,500 --> 00:01:40,041
I don’t remember them or know
their names, they were all masked

26
00:01:40,041 --> 00:01:41,833
Even their hands weren’t visible

27
00:01:46,500 --> 00:01:48,916
Interviewer: Have you
heard about women’s cells?

28
00:01:48,958 --> 00:01:52,750
Or cells for ISIS members
being punished inside this prison?

29
00:01:54,166 --> 00:01:56,458
There weren’t any in this place.

30
00:01:56,958 --> 00:01:58,500
Interviewer: There
were no women’s cells?

31
00:01:59,083 --> 00:02:02,875
There were cells for women, but not
for ISIS members themselves.

32
00:02:04,333 --> 00:02:09,166
This room was for
women, and that room too.

33
00:02:10,208 --> 00:02:12,166
Interviewer: And the rest of the
rooms, do you recall their purpose?

34
00:02:12,416 --> 00:02:15,166
No, I only remember
there was a hall here.

35
00:02:16,041 --> 00:02:19,875
In this hall, for major charges.

36
00:02:20,541 --> 00:02:25,000
For example, someone was caught
with a Kia truck transporting cigarettes

37
00:02:26,166 --> 00:02:29,750
And other materials they
used to bring from outside Mosul

38
00:02:34,583 --> 00:02:39,541
Interviewer: Can you describe the sound
you heard from the women’s cells?

39
00:02:41,208 --> 00:02:43,208
I heard their children’s
voices, I mean

40
00:02:44,166 --> 00:02:45,666
Their children crying

41
00:02:46,958 --> 00:02:48,750
From that window over there

42
00:02:55,583 --> 00:02:58,791
Interviewer: Do you have a memory
related to this spot in this corridor?

43
00:02:58,791 --> 00:02:59,833
With ISIS?

44
00:03:01,500 --> 00:03:06,083
I only remember that I entered this place
normally and left with my hand amputated.

45
00:03:12,458 --> 00:03:16,583
Interviewer: Did you notice display
screens showing ISIS videos in this yard?

46
00:03:17,333 --> 00:03:21,291
No, in the yard there weren’t
any, only in their official’s room.

47
00:03:21,833 --> 00:03:23,291
There was a screen

48
00:03:23,416 --> 00:03:26,041
Interviewer: The sharia judge’s room?
Witness: Yes
